message.body: @plus5keen Valid inputs are A, B, X, Y, L, R, Select, Start (Buttons and triggers), Up, Down, Left, Right (D Pad). It's exactly what you'd see if you looked at a Super NES controller! Typos work too! You can also find this help message in the stream description.

fragments.text: @plus5keen Valid inputs are A, B, X, Y, L, R, Select, Start (Buttons and triggers), Up, Down, Left, Right (D Pad). It's exactly what you'd see if you looked at a Super NES controller! Typos work too! You can also find this help message in the stream description.

message.body: Up to 5 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Right will press the B Button, press Up and press Right on the D Pad. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both press Left on the D Pad.

fragments.text: Up to 5 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Right will press the B Button, press Up and press Right on the D Pad. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both press Left on the D Pad.

message.body: Normal duration of inputs is 133 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by using spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

fragments.text: Normal duration of inputs is 133 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by using spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

message.body: Example: Up+Right+B;2000 A+X+Down;1000 *5 Will press Up and Right on the D Pad and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and X Buttons and press Down on the D Pad for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and *5 means the input will be executed once, then it will be repeated 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

message.body: Up to 5 different inputs can be executed at the same time by using + to combine inputs. Example: B+Up+Right will press the B Button, press Up and press Right on the D Pad. It is not needed to start your message with ! mark. Commands are NOT case sensitive: left and lEft will both press Left on the D Pad.

message.body: Normal duration of inputs is 133 milliseconds. You can separate multiple inputs by using spaces or commas to execute multiple inputs in rapid succession.

message.body: Example: Up+Right+B;2000 A+X+Down;1000 *5 Will press Up and Right on the D Pad and press the B Button for 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds), then press the A and X Buttons and press Down on the D Pad for 1000 milliseconds (1 second), and *5 means the input will be executed once, then it will be repeated 5 times. There is no delay between inputs.

There is no delay between inputs.

message.body: You can use square brackets to make smaller loops. Example: [A+B;1000 X+Y;500*4] Start [L+R Up+Left*2] 2 will press A+B then X+Y 4 times, then will press Start, then will press L+R then Up+Left 2 times, and everything will be repeated 2 times.

message.body: There is no delay between inputs, but sometimes you'll need a delay between inputs, you can use Wait or Stop to add a delay between inputs. Example: A Wait *255 will press the A Button for 133 milliseconds then wait for another 133 milliseconds, and will repeat that macro 255 times, basically mashing the A Button 256 times. Macros can be repeated up to 255 times. Up to 95 inputs can be chained in a macro.
